The paper deals with job scheduling in large-scale computing clusters, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of redundancy and checkpointing to tackle variability in job completion times suggests a focus on system dynamics and control (cs.SY) and performance analysis (cs.PF). The design of online scheduling algorithms involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
